<br>
The main OOC reason listed was to deny competitive players/guilds the opportunity to profit extensively from the wardens. I believe a paraphrase would be &quot;uberguild A farms the wardens to get all the primal they want, and then wakes the sleeper once another uberguild starts farming, to keep their status as the uberest of the uber&quot;.<br>
<br>
Another OOC reason I saw was a personal glory thing. Some folks play to get virtual feathers in their cap... to be the first to get an item or do a quest or whatever. Some of those people will wake the Sleeper just so they can be the ones who did it (they get the glory, such as it is). Some do it strictly for the fame of being the only ones who will ever wake the Sleeper, others believe if they don't, someone else will... and they don't want folks who aren't &quot;really&quot; entitled to the glory to get it.<br>
<br>
A few of the Sleepers on some apparently were apparently awakened by people who just refuse to believe that the critter is unkillable and the quest is a dead end. Despite multiple detailed reports from other servers. Kind of like l33t qu3st g33ks or something - they were confident that everyone else had just overlooked something, and they would be the folks who solved the real mystery.<br>
<br>
Finally, some people are 'complete solution' players. These are the people who aren't content to just win and finish the latest game, they have to have the highest 'score' - they have to do everything. I have a friend like this who has a really bad case and has to go back and replay Nintendo games, long after the fun is gone, because he can't rest unless he has all the possible points, every little side quest and easter egg and everything. Those folks might wake the Sleeper just because it is there - the same way my friend drinks the potion in the maze because it is there, even though he knows it is bad, because it is part of the game to do the whole maze.<br>
<br>
I know there were a couple more, but those are the ones I can remember at the moment. Shintou doesn't seem like he's here to get the best stuff for himself and deny anyone else. He seems far more interested in a rich storyline than in collecting firsts. He frankly doesn't seem like someone who is so immersed in the mechanics of the Verant lore that he just has to try to solve the developers puzzle. And I haven't noted him doing things just because they were coded... he seems quite willing to ignore parts of the game that don't interest him and play what does.<br>
<br>
The only OOC reason I saw listed that might apply to him was the &quot;just because it would be so darn cool to see&quot;. But then again, I would see him doing something like that in a roleplay context, so alot of people could be there for the event, rather than just him and a couple of guildies waking the Sleeper for their own personal amusement (and deaths). And that is counterbalanced by the fact that doing so closes off the option to see something else really cool (an intact Sleeper's Tomb) for everyone.<br>
<br>
Like I said, I don't know Shintou, except by what he posts. I could be a drooling idiot here. But you asked, so I gave you my best shot on why I hold the opinion I do.<br>
<br>
Shintou, of course, is free to tell me I am way off base and that he really is a l33t qu3st g33k who is gonna solve this Sleeper thing once and for all, dammit...<br>
